reviewText: My 2 and 4 year old boys love this movie. We borrowed it from the local library and they always wanted to renew it!

My grandson watches this two to three times a day. Thanks. The packaging was secure.
It came on time when it said it would.
This was a great and unique video explaining the different types of firetrucks, such as an airport firetruck.  It held the interest of 3-5 year olds and offered new information.

I bought the full DVD after seeing a segment on the net with my grandson.  It did not disappoint.  He is completely mesmerized by it, stopping all running around and playing.  He is completely captivated by the sights, sounds, and the MUSIC!  It's been a great buy giving lots of entertainment (and brief breaks for his mother!).

Hey this is a a great informational video, but it is for older kids.  My 2 year old son loves the intro song but loses interest when the talking starts.  However, the info is so accurate and practical I'm planning on using it to train rookies in the academy, haha!

This is a great video describing the contents of Lots & Lots of Fire Trucks Vol. 1 and Vol. 2 that's part of the #1 Best Selling As Seen On TV Lots and Lots of Series of DVDs. Just look up Lots and Lots of and you'll see the entire DVD series. My son is three years old and can't get enough of this DVD! There are lots of songs that teach fire safety that my son loves to sing along with! A must have for the toddler that loves fire trucks and fire fighters!

Like most kids, my kids love fire trucks, so this is right up there alley. The songs are fun and the pictures are very exciting. I also like the saftey things that are in this show. We have both videos and the boys wathcthem almost every day.
Excellent Video.  My 3 year old granddaughter loved it and her father, who is a fire professional, agreed that it is a great DVD for kids.
My grandson had Vol. 1 and LOVES Vol 2. Thanks!
My 5 year old son LOVES these he has watched it over and over the songs are catchy and seeing the fire trucks in action in all types of senecios and learning the firehouse history
Just okay, he likes better trains.

My two sons LOVE the Lots of Trucks and Lots of Trains, and I thought they would enjoy the Lots of Fire Trucks. This is more of a fire safety video, and how firemen do their jobs. Better for older kids.

My 3 yr old who is in love with everything firetrucks liked the video. He also really likes the theme song. He didn't however watch it as many times as I thought he would but it was still very good and useful. I hope to buy the other editions
Wearing his fireman hat and usually holding a fire truck Jonah enjoys watching this dvd over and over again and again.
